How can we read data from a file in Java?

a)    Using a Scanner in conjunction with a File object.
b)    By using object-oriented programming (OOP).
c)    The method System.file.readln method is the counterpoint to System.out.println and allows us to read files.
d)    Using the System.out.println command.
e)    All data on the computer is in binary, so the data can be read one bit at a time using the Bit data type.

Correct answer: a)
